I have to say that we have not come to this restaurant it moved from the Broadway location and settled back onto 12th avenue.  We came on a Sunday morning/afternoon (~12 noon) and we were seated right away.  However, it took another 20/25 minutes before someone came by to take our order.  We specifically asked about brunch because we were handed what seemed to be a dinner menu.  We were told that there was no brunch, but we're not even informed that breakfast was an option (we found that out later when a table next to us proceeded to order breakfast items).   After another another 10 minutes the waitress came back and brought what could only be classified as bread samples as opposed to a basket of bread.  We placed our order and tried to make a substitution and were emphatically told that it could not be done, again we heard someone else make a substitution later as well.  My mother inlaw, and my wife ordered cafe con leche and after waiting another 15 minutes she had to get up and go to the bar to let them know that we still had not received it as yet.  After finally getting the coffee we were again waiting for our food and noticed that a party that came after us and 3 other parties got their food before we did.  At last! We received our food order and I am sad to say we were disappointed.  The mofongo was dry, the pork was salty along with the back beans and my wife's steak came out cold.  It is with great excitement that I can say that I will not be returning back to this restaurant. And I can't get out of this place fast enough.

Great place to have some Cuban food. I'm from Florida so this place definitely hits the spot..!!

If you have a hankering for good old Cuban food without any bells and whistles, Floridita is the place for you. It's perfect for small or large parties, the prices are quite affordable when compared to the fancier Cuban places popping up throughout the city.  Floridita has stood the test of time, located in Harlem for decades now. The space has been renovated, the menu has been expanded but the staff nice, but is a little slow due to the size of the place. My recommendation: get a pitcher of their awesome Sangria and have a drink as you wait for your dinner.

The food it's ok at best. I think it's a little over priced. The service on the other hand is horrible, waited 1 1/2 for a delivery. Everytime i called they kept on telling me that the delivery guy left. The last time i call to tell the manager they hang up the phone on me.

This place is terrific!  Excellent paella, delicious Cuban sandwiches and great roast pork.  Love the plantains and white rice with beans.  Classic Cuban cuisine!  Great atmosphere, too!  Nice people, terrific wait staff, and clean place.  Friday nights are the best - live music!  I love this Floridita!

There is nothing cuban about this place. They might as well call it nondescript hispanic food. The food was not fresh (mostly cold and dry) and over priced for the low quality. I should have expected this. It is a huge place and only four customers. The waitress got our order wrong three times. It was a major sacrifice since I passed up on delicious ribs at Dinosaur next door. This restaurant is an embarrassment to cubans (at least one cuban).

Floridita offers an excellent customer service and nice environment if you are in the mood for spanish comfort food.  The slow roasted chicken is the best menu choice as well as their rice and bean and fried plantains.
